# Regression: re-registering a migration with the same name but a different body
# must fail with `MigrationHashMismatch`. Applied migrations are immutable; if
# we let the body silently change, environments would drift (one process saw
# the old body, another sees the new one, both think they're up to date).

(admin "CREATE MIGRATION 'm_change' { CREATE NAMESPACE app_change }")
!admin "CREATE MIGRATION 'm_change' { CREATE NAMESPACE app_changed }"
---
> Error CA_049
>   migration `m_change` content has changed since registration: was 0xe1945bbcd43b695a06cd129c8c9fe20f, now 0x152115678a52ebc5ac73cc06e49745cd
>
> HELP
>   applied migrations are immutable; revert the change or register a new migration with a different name
>
> NOTES
>   • the registered hash in the catalog does not match the hash of the supplied body+rollback
